adjectives.description: incognoscible (comparative more incognoscible, superlative most incognoscible)

entries.meaning: (rare, dated) Not capable of being known; incomprehensible.
examples: 6. The state of the law rendered more and more incognoscible. By wrapping up the real dispositions of the law in a covering of nonsense, the knowledge of it is rendered impossible to the bulk of the people.
